div.head:
Christian Behaviour;
OR,
The Fruits of true Christianity.

div.p:
Folly is bound up in the heart of a Child;
but the Rod of Correction will fetch it out,
Prov. 22. 15.

                  Secondly, But if none at the present
but unbelievers can be got to do thy labour;
Then,



                  'Tis true, in the Salvation of a natural
Son which is mentioned in the Parable;
This my Son was dead, and is alive again;
was lost, and is found; and they began to be
merry, Luke 15. 24.
